 * src/parseForest/filterOptions.c: corrected the printing of filtering options.

Thu Dec 13 15:10:34 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/gss/gss.c: corrected an off-by-one error. It was causing a segmentation 
   fault in some experiments.

Wed Dec 12 17:13:04 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/*: added some more stat counting (rejected GSS nodes) and removed some 
   redundant counting.

Tue Dec  4 11:45:13 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/commandLineInterface.c: added the -m flag to stop the parse tree from
   being output. Useful for performace comparisons with other tools.
 * src/parserOptions.{c,h}: added code to handle new flag.

Tue Dec  4 11:17:02 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parser/parserStatistics.{c,h}: commented out the code that collects and
   prints the stats on the number of edge visits done for each level. I don't
   think they are useful and should probably be completely removed.

Fri Nov 30 13:58:27 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/gss/gss.c: fixed bug 800. The currentLevel was being cleared after
   garbage collection was performed on the GSS. I think this is what caused sglr   to fail to terminate after the second parse was completed.

Mon Nov 26 18:06:32 EST 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * src/commandlineInterface.c: fixed one todo: a proper error message
   when the parse table file is not found.

