   svn+ssh://economop@svn.cwi.nl/sglr/branches/srnglr

Wed Aug 22 17:03:41 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * test/terms/postParsePriorityFilter.ppprio: regenerated because the forest's 
   count of ambiguities was out of date.

Wed Aug 22 16:59:45 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/commandLineInterface.c: typo in usage info.

Wed Aug 22 15:36:36 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: created an error message for when the filtering 
   removes all parse trees.

Wed Aug 22 14:29:10 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/Makefile.am: moved the sglr directories to the top of the header search
   path (list of -Idir options) so that they are the first that will be 
   searched by GCC. This fixes the error encountered during the compilation of 
   the sglr bundle -- aterm/aterm/list.h was being found instead of
   sglr/src/utils/list.h when compiling sglr.

Thu Aug 16 16:43:19 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * test/erroneousCommandLines: forgot to turn on the injection and preference 
   counting filters. 

Thu Aug 16 16:34:50 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filterOptions.c: switched off the injection and preference
   counting filters by default.
 * test/termCommandLines: switched on the injection and preference counting
   filters for the old regression tests. We should generate some new tests
   that test the new default behaviour.

Thu Aug 16 16:03:21 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * test/termsCommandLines: changed the cyclic regression tests so that the 
   injection and preference counting filters are switched off. These filters
   do not work correctly on cyclic trees! If an ambiguous node is encountered
   on the traversal of a 'counting' filter we assume that we have already
   counted all ambiguous branches (as filtering is done from the bottom up) 
   and therefore each branch must have an equal number of injections. As an 
   optimization we only traverse one of the branches. However, if the 
   ambiguous tree has a cyclic branch then the assumption does not hold and
   the filtering results depend on the order of the children of an ambiguous
   node. This caused the mdj.cycle regression test to fail in pgen.
 * test/terms/bi.asfix2.org: regenerated with the injection and preference
   counting filters switched off.

Wed Aug 15 15:16:49 CEST 2007 <{kooiker,storm}@cwi.nl>
 * src/Makefile.am: added sglr_la_LIBADD variable to let libtool resolve
   symbols defined in external libraries.
	
Fri Jul 13 15:58:49 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parser/parser.c: the wrong api function was being called. Fortunately 
   it was accessing the correct argument in the ATerm!

Fri Jul 13 11:59:23 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Made the "count number of ambiguities independent of position information"
   option a MAIN option. I'll probably make this the default behaviour and
   remove the option.

Fri Jul 13 11:10:05 CEST 2007 <{economop,kooiker,oktener}@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: Add function to count ambiguities independent
   of position in tree.

Fri Jul  6 13:35:58 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/inputString.c: if an input string is empty and IS_isEndOfString() is 
   called then ATtrue is returned.

Thu Jun 21 14:16:52 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parser/parser.c: changed the use of the forActorDelayed to match the 
   algorithmic description in Eelco's thesis. State nodes that are created by 
   rejected reductions now get added to the forActorDelayed and are only 
   processed once all nodes in the forActor have been processed. This fixes 
   the bug that resulted in some valid parse trees being incorrectly rejected. 
   However, this approach still results in some invalid parse trees not being
   filtered during parsing that get filtered in the post parse traversal.
 * test/grammars/TooManyTreesRejected.def: added regression test to ensure
   the reject bug that resulted in too many trees being filtered is not
   re-produced.

Tue May 15 15:51:37 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/commandLineInterface.c: fixed bug that prevented the -f flag from
   switching all filters off.
 * src/parseForest/filterOptions.c: tidied up code.

Mon May 14 16:59:44 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: removed some redundant checks on filtering
   options and fixed some places that filtering was done without correctly 
   checking the filtering options first. This should result in
   less trees being incorrectly filtered (removed) when certain filtering
   options are turned off (I think the reject filter continued removing trees
   even if the reject option was turned off). Presumably this will also improve 
   the performance of the filtering slightly.
   I'm planning of introducing some regression tests with different filtering
   options set. I'll use those tests to ensure that the filtering is correct. 
 * src/parseForest/filterOptions.c: when the -f flag is set all other filters
   are turned off. This makes the check during parsing more straight forward.

Wed May  9 19:04:14 CEST 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: reverted the code on unrolling cycles,
   which was experimental. Next time, we'll do it on a branch :-)
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: fixed a bug in the representation of cycles.
   Maximal innermost sharing does not work when you have cycles. The reason
   is of course that the identity of a tree containing a cycle is not
   defined by its children alone anymore. The bugfix turns off sharing
   for all levels that have a cycle in them. 
   WARNING: this may slow down the parser again, since we used a naive
   way of storing/retrieving which levels have cycles. To be improved
   probably by using a more efficient data-structure.

Tue May  8 10:13:32 CEST 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: fixed an incompatibility with previous
   versions. The indirect preference filter checked for user defined
   injections only, while previous versions checked for all injections.
   Since this version is to be fully backward compatible, I've have 
   changed it back. Also added some comments and optimized one
   test by taking the more easily computed inverse.

Thu May  3 13:54:28 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: implemented unrolling of cyclic parse forests.
 * src/parseForest/filterOptions.{c,h}: added unrolling of cycles as a 
   filtering option. It is turned off by default.
 * test/*: added new regression test.

Tue Apr 24 13:39:35 CEST 2007 <{economop,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: fixed the indirect preference filter. An
   assert was added checking a precondition (both tree being appl's before
   we get a prod from them). This assertion indeed failed. Added a test
   for the case when one of the trees is a character.

Tue Apr 24 11:25:02 CEST 2007 <{kooiker,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * restorebrackets: fixed a major bug, restore brackets generated
   illegal asfix for the brackets trees! 
 * Version of SGLR is 4.0 since the last merge.

Wed Apr 18 15:07:06 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: fixed null pointer exception.

Mon Apr 16 14:11:23 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Fixed parse table error handling for toolbus invocations.
 * test/erroneous/true.asfix2.org: regenerated because the error message 
   changed slightly due to the above fix.

Mon Apr 16 11:21:42 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * test/regressionTests.sh.src: added -x option to the command line arguments.

Fri Apr 13 12:01:53 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: added memoization to the ambiguity count
   traversal. The count now gives the number of ambiguities in the maximally
   shared representation of the parse tree.

Thu Apr 12 15:36:17 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: added an extra traversal of the final parse tree 
   to count the number of ambiguous nodes. This is a temporary fix to get 
   the asf-checker working again...

Tue Apr  3 11:51:40 CEST 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: corrected preference count filter. It's
   behaviour was changed during the refactoring which resulted in some 
   ambiguities (the asf equations of the Sdf2-Normalization) not being
   filtered correctly.

Wed Mar 21 11:07:34 CET 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * src/{toolbusInterface.c,sglr.idef.src}: reintroduced possibility to
   activate preference counting and injection counting filters with an
   option in the ToolBus interface script to SGLR. This is needed for
   backward compatibility when parsing equations.

Tue Mar 20 13:44:26 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseTable/parseTable.c,parseTableBuilder.c: tidied up ATwarnings.

Tue Mar 20 13:35:28 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * test/regressionTests.sh.src: tidied up script.

Thu Mar 15 16:06:44 CET 2007 <{economop,kooiker}@cwi.nl>
 * restorebrackets/src/restorebrackets-main.c: fixed incorrect merge

Wed Mar 14 15:17:46 CET 2007 <{economop,kooiker}@cwi.nl>
 * Merged sglr-refactored branch into the trunk.

Wed Mar 14 14:14:34 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Removed the java directory.

Tue Mar 13 13:27:01 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Changed the TODO c-comments to doxygen \todo comments.

Mon Mar  5 13:56:05 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/gss/shiftQueue.c: the shift queue was implemented as a stack and not a
   queue. This resulted in the GSS state nodes being processed in a different
   order to what was done on the trunk version of sglr. This caused the 
   parse-time reject filtering to break, which in turn caused the post-parse 
   filtering to do more work. We implemented the shift queue as a queue and
   noticed a ~1% speed-up for the SDF grammar example. Unfortunately this 
   "worst case" behaviour cannot be prevented in the general case, but at 
   least the behaviour of this branch is now consistent with the trunk.
 * src/gss/reductionPath.{c,h}: added a print function to aid debugging. 

Fri Mar  2 11:14:49 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/sglr-termstore.{c,h}: added forgotten term-store code.

Thu Mar  1 19:57:55 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/Makefile.am: added CPPFLAGS option to use the fast (macro) api's.
 * src/gss/gssNodeList.{c,h}, src/gss/gssEdgeList.{c,h}: rewrote getHead() and
   getTail using macros which results in an ~4% speedup. Including the small
   (~1%) saving that we made by introducing macros into apigen we are now 
   slightly faster than the trunk version of sglr that still uses PIC! 
   Unfortunately, we are still ~14% slower than the trunk without-pic, but this 
   will hopefully disappear if we introduce more macros into apigen.

Mon Feb 26 15:37:59 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/parseForest/filters.c: introduced a term store from asc-support to 
   avoid reversing the children of a tree during the priority filter. This 
   results in a 3% speedup. (I forgot to add the term-store code in this
   check-in. I did it later...)

Mon Feb  5 17:38:25 CET 2007 <{economop,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * Merged revisions 21189-21203 via svnmerge from 
   svn+ssh://economop@svn.cwi.nl/sglr/branches/sglr-reject-postparse
   This was the refactored filtering done in the srnglr branch.
 * src/*.c: after profiling we reimplement the OPT_ options library,
   and removed ambtracker. We also reimplemented the way we analyze
   injections, and removed all uses of lookupLabel. Altogether this
   accounts for 70% time savings. We are still optimizing though...
 * Reimplemented the code and data structures that are used to determine if a 
   production is an injection or not. Removed lookupLabel(), which was only 
   used in the injection filtering, and reimplemented the production lookups. 
   This resulted in a significant speedup.
 * src/utils/list.{c,h}: introduced macros for expensive functions found in
   the profiling.
 * src/utils/memoryManagerGenerator.h: changed so that 2 pools are used:
   - new_pool, where the memory is freshly allocated;
   - reuse_pool, where the memory is freed and then reused.
   The reuse pool allows the optimisation of not protecting the address of
   reused ATerms. This made a huge saving in memory consumption ~200MBs!
   Also, malloc now uses a reference parameter to returns 0 if the memory was
   re-used and 1 if not.
 * src/sglrInterface.c: changed the initial ATerm table size and Afun class
   size. We need to allow the user to do this on the command line. This may
   now not be necessary because of the improvements made during profiling.
 * src/gss/gssEdge.{c,h}: introduced counting of the edges created in the GSS.
   This is debug code, and should be hidden. However, initial experiments show
   that the number of edges created differ in this branch from the trunk --
   slightly worrying...but it could just be an error in the counting.

Fri Feb  2 11:34:40 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * src/sglr.c: added code to increase heap size etc of ATerms.

Wed Jan 31 13:16:08 CET 2007 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Merged revisions 21126-21188 via svnmerge from 
   svn+ssh://economop@svn.cwi.nl/sglr/branches/sglr-reject-postparse

