Fri Sep  1 16:51:54 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Moved documentation around.

Thu Aug 31 17:33:09 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added even more comments and documentation.

Wed Aug 30 16:47:14 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added comments.

Tue Aug 29 16:57:52 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added a new filter flag, -t, that only performs direct preference filtering.    Only one of the (in)direct preference filters can be performed, not both.
 * Added comments.
 * Added a regression test (PostParsePriorityFilter) that triggers the bug in 
   the post parse filtering of priorities. I corrected the term used in
   the regression tests manually.
 * Re-wrote the post-parse priority filtering as the previous implementation
   did not work correctly in certain circumstances (see previous message).
 
Tue Aug 22 14:01:28 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Located bug in |priorityFilter| which prevents the post parse filtering of 
   priority conflicts separated by injection chains with more than one nested 
   ambiguity cluster. Still needs to be refactored.
 * Corrected behaviour of main filter flag.
 * Updated the filtering names in the usage information.
 * Corrected handling of filter on start symbol option.
 * Removed #inAmbs parameter from filterTreeRecursive as is not used.

Wed Jun 28 17:39:37 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Corrected the sglr handling of options in the commandLineInterface and 
   toolbusInterface.
 * Added comments to |filters.c|.

Tue Jun 27 15:18:41 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * configure.in: added AM_MAINTAINER_MODE.
 * Makefile.am, doc/Makefile.am: corrected the doc generation.

Fri Jun 23 16:49:19 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Refactored names in |filters.c|.
 * Added comments.
 * Changed eagerness flags in |filterOptions| to preference.

Fri Jun 23 09:46:50 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Changed restoreBrackets to use the newly refactored sglr.

Thu Jun 22 17:48:14 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Moved functions from |filters.c| to |MEPT-utils.c| and |parseTable.c|.

Thu Jun 22 16:10:52 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added files |filterStats.{c,h}| that were forgotten in previous commit.
 * Corrected errors in |filters.c|, which were introduced during the previous 
   revision's refactoring, that caused the TestCobol regression test
   to fail.
 * Added check for NULL tree before trying to create and return a parse tree 
   in FLT_filterTree(). This caused an assert to be triggerred for the Reject 
   regression test.
 * Reviewed comments and made function names consistent in |filters.c|.

Wed Jun 21 18:18:13 CEST 2006 <{jurgen,economop}@cwi.nl>
 * We refactored all of |filters.c| which caused changes in |parser.c| and 
   |ambi-tables.c|, among other files. The TestCobol regression test fails. It
   appears to not filter an avoided tree. Probably an error in 
   SG_FilterArgsRecursive(). We'll comment further tomorrow ;-)

Tue Jun 20 18:24:36 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added doxygen comments.
 * Partly refactored function names in |filters.c|, specifically renaming all
   instances of eagerness to preference.

Tue Jun 20 16:30:40 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Refactored all counting from |filters.c| to the new file |filterStats.c|.
 * Renamed the 'eagerness' counts to 'preference' counts.
 * As a result of the separation of counting from |filters.c| the dependency
   from |ambi-tables.c| was removed.

