   int instead.
 * Replaced SG_A_STATE() with api function.

Tue Jun 20 10:47:17 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added Doxygen comments to |inputString.c| and |inputStringBuilder.c|.
 * Refactored |inputStringBuilder.c| by moving the allocationn and
   deallocation of the input string to |inputString.c|.
 * Removed charInCharClass() from |inputString.c| and used function in
   MEPT-utils.
 * Refactored recursive definition of checkLookahead() to an iterative
   definition.
 * Use PTBL api for the checking of lookahead reductions.
 * Regenerated Follower.tbl in the regression tests to use the new style 
   lookahead reductions.

Fri Jun  9 14:45:16 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Added Doxygen comments to files in the src directory. Not everything is 
   documented yet, but it's a start!
 * Added the new docs directory to svn. It contains the configuration and
   mainPage files of Doxygen. I set the svn:ignore property so that the
   generated html and latex directories are ignored.

Thu May 18 14:02:39 CEST 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Updated parse tables in regression tests to use the apified version of
   pgen:
   - Action2.def: declared undeclared sorts
   - AmbiRules.def: declared undeclared sorts
   - Casl.def: removed unused sorts and declared undeclared sorts. However,
   there are still some unresolved problems: Qual-Pred-Name is used, but
   undefined; and there is an "inconsistent right-hand side in priorities" on
   line 398 col 4: "(" Term ")" -> Simple-Term. This grammar is probably not
   correct Casl, but I have not changed it since it caused a lot of errors in 
   earlier versions of SGLR.
   from the 'real world' I didn't fix these two issues.
   - Expression.def: uses an "illegal attribute: non-assoc" on line 85, col 1
   and line 29. This also was not changed since it may cause unexpected
   behaviour.
   - Prefer.def: declared undeclared sorts, but ImportSet is still undefined.
   I left this so as not to change the behaviour of the regression tests.
   - Risla.def: removed unused sort and declared undeclared sorts.
   - RobsReject.def: Added Main module.
   - SimpleCobol.def: removed unused sort. There is a bug in sdf-checker that
   causes the final module in this grammar to be missed. This results in the
   error 'undefined symbol used on line 220, col 4: Str'
   - TestCobol.def: declared undeclared sorts.
   - Added the new SDF2 grammar and replaced the old table the parse table.

