Mon Jan 23 15:15:09 CET 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Changed the toolbus interface in |sglr.idef|.

Mon Jan 23 12:03:39 CET 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Incorporated handling of cyclic parse forests in the filtering.
 * Added new filter: 'Remove cycles' under the '-fc' option. If the filter is 
   active, all cycles are removed from all ambiguity clusters. The default 
   setting is off.
 * Moved regression tests |bi.cycle| and |mdj.cycle2| from test/erroneous to 
   test/terms as cycles in the parse forest no longer cause errors.

Mon Jan 16 17:07:35 CET 2006 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Intermediate commit for handling of cycles in the filtering. 
   Still need to add PT_makeTreeCycle(). 
   New files created:
   - parseForest/levels.{c,h}
 * If the input string is created with IS_createInputStringFromString then the
   path is set to |_noPath_|.

Thu Dec 22 15:14:09 CET 2005 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Errors are now created with the use of ErrorManager. A summary is 
   created that contains a list of errors so regression tests have been updated.
 * Updated true.nss regression test.
 * Changed regress-terms.sh.src to notify if atdiff fails and error-diff 
   succeeds.
 * Added |slgr.c| and refactored the main function into it with support for
   toolbus invocation of parser.
 * Changed messages passed back to the toolbus to |parse-succeeded| and 
   |parse-failed|. A successful parse contains a parse tree or forest and
   possibly an error summary if the ErrorOnAmbiguity flag is set. A failed
   parse only contains an error summary.

Fri Jul 22 17:06:44 CEST 2005 <{economop,kooiker}@cwi.nl>
 * Added |reverseList| function to |list.c|, |GSSNodeList| and |GSSEdgeList| 
   to aid debugging.
 * Refactored function and variable names to be consistent.
 * Renamed the following files:
   - sglr-interface.c  -> sglrInterface.c
   - sglr.h            -> sglrInterface.h
   - sglr-main.c       -> commandLineInterface.c
   - tool.c            -> toolbusInterface.c
   - tool.h            -> toolbusInterface.h
 * Added commandLineInterface.h
 * Renamed the type |parse_table| -> |ParseTable|.
 * Renamed |sglrInterface.c| functions:
   - SGopenLanguageFromTerm() -> SGLR_setParseTable()
   - SGopenLanguage()         -> SGLR_loadParseTable()
 * Added ptable-support to configure.in
 * Changed the type of the parse table that is passed into SGLR: 
   |ATerm| -> |PTBL_ParseTable|.
 * Created inputString.{c,h}. 
    - No longer append '\n' to input string. This was an error that caused the 
      Reject regression test to fail with an incorrect error ('\n' unexpected
      instead of eof unexpected).
    - Hid implementation of inputString.
    - Moved |SG_CharInCharClass| |SG_checkLookAhead| (used by the reducer 
      with lookahead) from parser to input string.
    - '\0' is only considered as a valid token if the input string is 
      created via the public functions |createInputStringFromBytes| or 
      |createInputStringFromFile|.
    - Moved positional info from parser to inputString.
 * Added more details of success and failure of individual regression tests 
   to |regress-terms.src.sh|.
 * Updated Reject regression test after above InputString fix.
 * Removed the '\n' printed at the end of the result.
 * Changed format of error messages.
 * Extracted filtering, yielding and cycledetection from SG_parse and added it
   to sglrInterface.
 * Added path to internal parsetable datastructure to help creating error 
   messages. 
 * r.rjct test fails because of the rejections done at parse time. They  killed
   the tree and caused an eof parse error. By doing the postparse filtering we
   get a NULL tree instead.
 
Thu Jun 30 14:28:11 CEST 2005 <economop@cwi.nl, jurgenv@cwi.nl, kooiker@cwi.nl>
 * Moved all |#define| definitions from src into temporary 'macros.h'.
 * Removed getopt.h, getopt.c getopt1.c and addded #include <unistd.h> instead.
 * Removed the #ifdef and #indef WIN32 uses.
 * Removed the long options from regress-terms.sh.src.
 * Removed -m flag which was the inverse of the -2 flag
 * Moved default values of options to topical initializeDefaultOptions functions.* Removed -b flag, which was the inverse of the -t flag
 * Usage information prints the real default values, instead of the current
   values.
 * Renamed forest.[ch] to filters.[ch]
 * Added forest.h which contains the definitions of tree and forest
 * Put printStatusBar in utils/statusBar.[ch]
 * Took include of parse-table.h from sglr.h
 * Moved definitions of parse-table and forest types to parse-table.h
   and forest.h respectively


