Wed Jun 29 09:47:12 CEST 2005 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Made the naming convention of variables and functions consistent.
 * Added ATerror messages when no more memory can be allocated.
 * Updated comments.

Tue Jun 28 15:24:51 CEST 2005 <economop@cwi.nl>
 * Refactored sglr directory structure:
   - created src directory to store all source files used in sglr. The src 
     directory contains the sglr interface files, the sglr library (libsglr.a)
     and five sub-directories listed below:
     1) gss 
	 Extracted entire GSS data structure (stack.c) and all searching and 
	 accessing functions (parser.c). All memory management and garbage 
	 collection was also separated (stack.c & parser.c).

	 The files included are listed below:
	  gss.c,                  gss.h
	  gssNode.c,              gssNode-api.h, gssNode-data.h 
	  gssEdge.c,              gssEdge-api.h, gssEdge-data.h 
	  gssNodeList.c,          gssNodeList.h
	  gssEdgeList.c,          gssEdgeList.h
	  gssGarbageCollector.c,  gssGarbageCollector.h 
	  reductionPath.c,        reductionPath.h
	  shiftQueue.c,           shiftQueue.h

     2) parseForest
	 ambi-tables.c,           ambi-tables.h
	 forest.c,                forest.h
	 
     3) parseTable
	 parseTable.c,            parseTable.h
     4) parser
	 parser.c,                parser.c
     5) utils
	 bitmap.c,                bitmap.h
	 getopt.c,                getopt.h
	 list.c,                  list.h
	 marking.c,               marking.h
	 - 			  memalloc.h
	 -                        memoryManagerGenerator.h, 
	 posmap.c, 		  posmap.h
	 rsrc-usage.c,		  rsrc-usage.h

     Each sub-directory contains its own makefile and non-installed libraries 
     to allow compilation.

 * Moved libsglr.a (the installed library for sglr) and sglr (the binary 
   executable) into the src directory.

 * Removed libsglr directory.

 * Removed sglr directory.

 * Created this changeLog file to allow easier merging of branches when the 
   refactoring is complete.

Tue Jun 21 09:29:17 CEST 2005 <{economop,kooiker,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * Commit before restructuring directory structure.
	
Fri Jun 17 16:02:55 CEST 2005 <{economop,kooiker,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * Factored out GSSNode and GSSEdge from GSS
 * Standardized functionnames in GSSList 
 * libsglr/{GGSList.c,GSSEdge.c,GSSNode.c}: Factored out all memory management
   code that contained smart tricks for preallocation and reuse of memory.
   Four instances changed to one local implementation.
   Deobfuscated the implementation, and then wrapped it in a macro such
   that type safe instantiations can be generated for each new struct.
   The macro is called GenerateMemoryManager and has a number of type
   arguments.

Wed Jun 15 17:45:37 CEST 2005 <{economop,kooiker,jurgenv}@cwi.nl>
 * Refactored stack.c into GSS, GSSMemoryManagement and GSSList
 * Refactor variable names into descriptive names
 * Added comments in memory management
 * Corrected memory leak 
 * Removed GENERIC_POOL_ALLOC

